gene.set.statistics.name: microtubule organizing center organization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a microtubule organizing center, a structure from which microtubules grow.

gene.set.statistics.name: actomyosin structure organization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures containing both actin and myosin or paramyosin. The myosin may be organized into filaments.

gene.set.statistics.name: gene silencing by RNA
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process in which RNA molecules inactivate expression of target genes.

gene.set.statistics.name: primary miRNA processing
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process involved in the conversion of a primary microRNA transcript into a pre-microRNA molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: pre-miRNA processing
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process involved in the conversion of a pre-microRNA transcript into a mature microRNA molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of histone modification
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the covalent alteration of a histone.

gene.set.statistics.name: animal organ regeneration
gene.set.statistics.description: The regrowth of a lost or destroyed animal organ.

gene.set.statistics.name: axon regeneration
gene.set.statistics.description: The regrowth of axons following their loss or damage.

gene.set.statistics.name: septin ring organization
gene.set.statistics.description: Control of the formation, spatial distribution, and breakdown of the septin ring.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of microtubule polymerization or depolymerization
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule polymerization or depolymerization by the addition or removal of tubulin heterodimers from a microtubule.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of microtubule polymerization
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule polymerization.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of microtubule polymerization
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule polymerization.

gene.set.statistics.name: cytoplasmic microtubule organization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of structures formed of microtubules and associated proteins in the cytoplasm of a cell.

gene.set.statistics.name: RNA 3'-end processing
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of an RNA molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: mRNA 3'-end processing
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of an mRNA molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: anaphase-promoting complex-dependent catabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds, initiated by the covalent attachment of ubiquitin, with ubiquitin-protein ligation catalyzed by the anaphase-promoting complex, and mediated by the proteasome.

gene.set.statistics.name: SCF-dependent proteasomal ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds, initiated by the covalent attachment of ubiquitin, with ubiquitin-protein ligation catalyzed by an SCF (Skp1/Cul1/F-box protein) complex, and mediated by the proteasome.

gene.set.statistics.name: rRNA methylation
gene.set.statistics.description: The posttranscriptional addition of methyl groups to specific residues in an rRNA molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: neuron projection development
gene.set.statistics.description: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron projection over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A neuron projection is any process extending from a neural cell, such as axons or dendrites (collectively called neurites).

gene.set.statistics.name: posttranslational protein targeting to membrane, translocation
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which a protein translocates through the ER membrane posttranslationally.

gene.set.statistics.name: biomineral tissue development
gene.set.statistics.description: Formation of hard tissues that consist mainly of inorganic compounds, and also contain a small amounts of organic matrices that are believed to play important roles in their formation.

gene.set.statistics.name: actin rod assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The assembly of actin rods, a cellular structure consisting of parallel, hexagonally arranged actin tubules.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of pseudopodium assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of pseudopodia.

gene.set.statistics.name: retinal ganglion cell axon guidance
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which the migration of an axon growth cone of a retinal ganglion cell (RGC) is directed to its target in the brain in response to a combination of attractive and repulsive cues.

gene.set.statistics.name: Ran protein signal transduction
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals within the cell that are mediated by a member of the Ran family of proteins switching to a GTP-bound active state.

gene.set.statistics.name: T cell costimulation
gene.set.statistics.description: The process of providing, via surface-bound receptor-ligand pairs, a second, antigen-independent, signal in addition to that provided by the T cell receptor to augment T cell activation.

gene.set.statistics.name: replication fork processing
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which a DNA replication fork that has stalled is restored to a functional state and replication is restarted. The stalling may be due to DNA damage, DNA secondary structure, bound proteins, dNTP shortage, or other causes.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of cellular metabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of protein-containing complex assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein complex assembly.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of protein-containing complex assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein complex assembly.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of vesicle fusion
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of vesicle fusion
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of protein ubiquitination
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of ubiquitin groups to a protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of protein ubiquitination
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of ubiquitin groups to a protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of protein ubiquitination
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of ubiquitin groups to a protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of protein modification process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the covalent alteration of one or more amino acid residues within a protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: keratinization
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which the cytoplasm of the outermost cells of the vertebrate epidermis is replaced by keratin. Keratinization occurs in the stratum corneum, feathers, hair, claws, nails, hooves, and horns.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of mRNA 3'-end processing
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mRNA 3'-end processing, any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of an mRNA molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of mRNA 3'-end processing
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mRNA 3'-end processing.

gene.set.statistics.name: nuclear membrane reassembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The reformation of the nuclear membranes following their breakdown in the context of a normal process.

gene.set.statistics.name: chromatin assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The assembly of DNA, histone proteins, other associated proteins, and sometimes RNA, into chromatin structure, beginning with the formation of the basic unit, the nucleosome, followed by organization of the nucleosomes into higher order structures, ultimately giving rise to a complex organization of specific domains within the nucleus.

gene.set.statistics.name: ruffle organization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a ruffle, a projection at the leading edge of a crawling cell.

gene.set.statistics.name: actin cytoskeleton reorganization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in dynamic structural changes to the arrangement of constituent parts of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of exit from mitosis
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the rate of progression from anaphase/telophase (high mitotic CDK activity) to G1 (low mitotic CDK activity).

gene.set.statistics.name: mitotic G1 DNA damage checkpoint signaling
gene.set.statistics.description: A signal transduction process that contributes to a mitotic cell cycle G1/S transition DNA damage checkpoint.

gene.set.statistics.name: hemidesmosome assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: Assembly of hemidesmosomes, integrin-containing protein complexes that bind to laminin in the basal lamina. Hemidesmosomes form the contact between the basal surface of epithelial cells and the underlying basal lamina.

gene.set.statistics.name: activation of phospholipase D activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that initiates the activity of inactive phospholipase D.

gene.set.statistics.name: cell-substrate adhesion
gene.set.statistics.description: The attachment of a cell to the underlying substrate via adhesion molecules.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of fever generation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of fever generation.

gene.set.statistics.name: receptor internalization
gene.set.statistics.description: A receptor-mediated endocytosis process that results in the movement of receptors from the plasma membrane to the inside of the cell. The process begins when cell surface receptors are monoubiquitinated following ligand-induced activation. Receptors are subsequently taken up into endocytic vesicles from where they are either targeted to the lysosome or vacuole for degradation or recycled back to the plasma membrane.

gene.set.statistics.name: synaptic vesicle fusion to presynaptic active zone membrane
gene.set.statistics.description: Fusion of the membrane of a synaptic vesicle with the presynaptic active zone membrane, thereby releasing its cargo neurotransmitters into the synaptic cleft.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of synaptic vesicle fusion to presynaptic active zone membrane
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of synaptic vesicle fusion to the presynaptic membrane.

gene.set.statistics.name: plasminogen activation
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which inactive plasminogen is processed to active plasmin. This process includes cleavage at an internal Arg-Val site to form an N-terminal A-chain and C-terminal B-chain held together by a disulfide bond, and can include further proteolytic cleavage events to remove the preactivation peptide.

gene.set.statistics.name: killing of cells of other organism
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process in an organism that results in the killing of cells of another organism, including in some cases the death of the other organism. Killing here refers to the induction of death in one cell by another cell, not cell-autonomous death due to internal or other environmental conditions.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of myelination
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the formation of a myelin sheath around nerve axons.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of myelination
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the formation of a myelin sheath around nerve axons.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of protein stability
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that affects the structure and integrity of a protein, altering the likelihood of its degradation or aggregation.

gene.set.statistics.name: protein destabilization
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that decreases the stability of a protein, making it more vulnerable to degradative processes or aggregation.

gene.set.statistics.name: lipopolysaccharide-mediated signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a lipopolysaccharide (LPS) to a receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription. Lipopolysaccharides are major components of the outer membrane of Gram-negative bacteria, making them prime targets for recognition by the immune system.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of lipopolysaccharide-mediated signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of signaling in response to detection of lipopolysaccharide.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to nutrient levels
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus reflecting the presence, absence, or concentration of nutrients.

gene.set.statistics.name: cellular response to extracellular stimulus
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an extracellular stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: cellular response to nutrient levels
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus reflecting the presence, absence, or concentration of nutrients.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of synaptic plasticity
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that increases synaptic plasticity, the ability of synapses to change as circumstances require. They may alter function, such as increasing or decreasing their sensitivity, or they may increase or decrease in actual numbers.

gene.set.statistics.name: TOR signaling
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals mediated by TOR (Target of rapamycin) proteins, members of the phosphoinositide (PI) 3-kinase related kinase (PIKK) family that act as serine/threonine kinases in response to nutrient availability or growth factors.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of chromatin silencing
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin silencing.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of protein autophosphorylation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of addition of the phosphorylation by a protein of one or more of its own residues.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of protein autophosphorylation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents or decreases the rate of the phosphorylation by a protein of one or more of its own residues.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of protein autophosphorylation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the phosphorylation by a protein of one or more of its own residues.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to corticosteroid
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a corticosteroid hormone stimulus. A corticosteroid is a steroid hormone that is produced in the adrenal cortex. Corticosteroids are involved in a wide range of physiologic systems such as stress response, immune response and regulation of inflammation, carbohydrate metabolism, protein catabolism, blood electrolyte levels, and behavior. They include glucocorticoids and mineralocorticoids.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of fatty acid beta-oxidation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of fatty acid bbeta-oxidation.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of fatty acid beta-oxidation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of fatty acid beta-oxidation.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of TOR signaling
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of TOR signaling.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of TOR signaling
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of TOR signaling.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of insulin secretion
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of insulin.

gene.set.statistics.name: mitochondrial DNA metabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving mitochondrial DNA.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of translational initiation in response to stress
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate of translation initiation as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of endodeoxyribonuclease activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endodeoxyribonuclease activity, the hydrolysis of ester linkages within deoxyribonucleic acid by creating internal breaks.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of NF-kappaB transcription factor activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of the transcription factor NF-kappaB.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of protein binding
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein binding.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of protein binding
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein binding.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to food
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a food stimulus; food is anything which, when taken into the body, serves to nourish or build up the tissues or to supply body heat.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of response to food
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to a food stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: activation of protein kinase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that initiates the activity of an inactive protein kinase.

gene.set.statistics.name: activation of protein kinase B activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive enzyme protein kinase B.

gene.set.statistics.name: telomere organization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of telomeres, terminal regions of a linear chromosome that include the telomeric DNA repeats and associated proteins.

gene.set.statistics.name: telomere maintenance via semi-conservative replication
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which telomeric DNA is synthesized semi-conservatively by the conventional replication machinery and telomeric accessory factors as part of cell cycle DNA replication.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of telomere maintenance
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process that affects and monitors the activity of telomeric proteins and the length of telomeric DNA.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of telomere maintenance
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a process that affects and monitors the activity of telomeric proteins and the length of telomeric DNA.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of telomere maintenance via telomerase
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of telomeric repeats by telomerase.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of telomere maintenance via telomerase
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of telomeric repeats by telomerase.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of synaptic transmission, GABAergic
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of GABAergic synaptic transmission, the process of communication from a neuron to another neuron across a synapse using the neurotransmitter gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA).

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of actin filament bundle assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of actin filament bundles.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of actin filament bundle assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of actin filament bundles.

gene.set.statistics.name: secretory granule localization
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process in which a secretory granule is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within the cell.

gene.set.statistics.name: methylation
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which a methyl group is covalently attached to a molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: IMP salvage
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process which produces inosine monophosphate from derivatives of it, without de novo synthesis.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of cellular protein metabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving a protein, occurring at the level of an individual cell.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of protein polymerization
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the process of creating protein polymers.

gene.set.statistics.name: peripheral nervous system myelin maintenance
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which the structure and material content of mature peripheral nervous system myelin is kept in a functional state.

gene.set.statistics.name: myelin assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which the wraps of cell membrane that constitute myelin are laid down around an axon in the central or peripheral nervous system.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of chondrocyte differentiation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chondrocyte differentiation.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of chondrocyte differentiation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of chondrocyte differentiation.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to estradiol
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of stimulus by estradiol, a C18 steroid hormone hydroxylated at C3 and C17 that acts as a potent estrogen.

gene.set.statistics.name: intracellular cholesterol transport
gene.set.statistics.description: The directed movement of cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3-beta-ol, within cells.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of intracellular cholesterol transport
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of cholesterol within cells.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of intracellular transport
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances within cells.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of intracellular transport
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances within cells.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of intracellular transport
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances within cells.

gene.set.statistics.name: DNA geometric change
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which a transformation is induced in the geometry of a DNA double helix, resulting in a change in twist, writhe, or both, but with no change in linking number. Includes the unwinding of double-stranded DNA by helicases.

gene.set.statistics.name: melanosome transport
gene.set.statistics.description: The directed movement of melanosomes into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of sodium:proton antiporter activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops or reduces the activity of a sodium:hydrogen antiporter, which catalyzes the reaction: Na+(out) + H+(in) = Na+(in) + H+(out).

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of sodium:proton antiporter activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the activity of a sodium:hydrogen antiporter, which catalyzes the reaction: Na+(out) + H+(in) = Na+(in) + H+(out).

gene.set.statistics.name: lysosome localization
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process in which a lysosome is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of phospholipase A2 activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the activity of the enzyme phospholipase A2.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of phospholipase A2 activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the activity of the enzyme phospholipase A2.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of proteasomal ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds, initiated by the covalent attachment of ubiquitin, and mediated by the proteasome.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of proteasomal ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds, initiated by the covalent attachment of ubiquitin, and mediated by the proteasome.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of proteasomal ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds, initiated by the covalent attachment of ubiquitin, and mediated by the proteasome.

gene.set.statistics.name: protein modification by small protein conjugation
gene.set.statistics.description: A protein modification process in which one or more groups of a small protein, such as ubiquitin or a ubiquitin-like protein, are covalently attached to a target protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: endocytic recycling
gene.set.statistics.description: The directed movement of membrane-bounded vesicles from endosomes back to the plasma membrane, a trafficking pathway that promotes the recycling of internalized transmembrane proteins.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of cytokinesis
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the division of the cytoplasm of a cell and its separation into two daughter cells.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of cytokinesis
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the division of the cytoplasm of a cell, and its separation into two daughter cells.

gene.set.statistics.name: endoplasmic reticulum calcium ion homeostasis
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of calcium ions within the endoplasmic reticulum of a cell or between the endoplasmic reticulum and its surroundings.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of endoplasmic reticulum calcium ion concentration
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that increases the concentration of calcium ions in the endoplasmic reticulum.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of endoplasmic reticulum calcium ion concentration
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that decreases the concentration of calcium ions in the endoplasmic reticulum.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of type I interferon production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of type I interferon production. Type I interferons include the interferon-alpha, beta, delta, episilon, zeta, kappa, tau, and omega gene families.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of type I interferon production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of type I interferon production. Type I interferons include the interferon-alpha, beta, delta, episilon, zeta, kappa, tau, and omega gene families.

gene.set.statistics.name: Rab protein signal transduction
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals within the cell that are mediated by a member of the Rab family of proteins switching to a GTP-bound active state.

gene.set.statistics.name: Rap protein signal transduction
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals within the cell that are mediated by a member of the Rap family of proteins switching to a GTP-bound active state.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of Rap protein signal transduction
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of Rap protein signal transduction.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to lipopolysaccharide
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a lipopolysaccharide stimulus; lipopolysaccharide is a major component of the cell wall of gram-negative bacteria.

gene.set.statistics.name: developmental process
gene.set.statistics.description: A biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition.

gene.set.statistics.name: cytokinetic process
gene.set.statistics.description: A cellular process that is involved in cytokinesis (the division of the cytoplasm of a cell and its separation into two daughter cells).

gene.set.statistics.name: maintenance of protein location in cell
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process in which a protein is maintained in a specific location within, or in the membrane of, a cell, and is prevented from moving elsewhere.

gene.set.statistics.name: DNA duplex unwinding
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which interchain hydrogen bonds between two strands of DNA are broken or 'melted', generating a region of unpaired single strands.

gene.set.statistics.name: endosome to lysosome transport via multivesicular body sorting pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: The directed movement of substances from endosomes to lysosomes by a pathway in which molecules are sorted into multivesicular bodies, which then fuse with the lysosome.

gene.set.statistics.name: late endosome to vacuole transport via multivesicular body sorting pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: The directed movement of substances from endosomes to vacuoles by a pathway in which molecules are sorted into multivesicular bodies, which then fuse with the vacuole.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of phosphoprotein phosphatase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops or reduces the activity of a phosphoprotein phosphatase.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of phosphoprotein phosphatase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the activity of a phosphoprotein phosphatase.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to retinoic acid
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a retinoic acid stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: protein exit from endoplasmic reticulum
gene.set.statistics.description: The directed movement of proteins from the endoplasmic reticulum.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of microvillus length
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that modulates the length of a microvillus.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of microvillus assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that modulates the formation of a microvillus.

gene.set.statistics.name: mitochondrial translation
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a protein in a mitochondrion. This is a ribosome-mediated process in which the information in messenger RNA (mRNA) is used to specify the sequence of amino acids in the protein; the mitochondrion has its own ribosomes and transfer RNAs, and uses a genetic code that differs from the nuclear code.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to progesterone
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a progesterone stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of interleukin-6 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-6 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of chemokine production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of chemokine production.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of interferon-gamma production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of interferon-gamma production. Interferon-gamma is also known as type II interferon.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of interleukin-12 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-12 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of interleukin-2 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-2 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of interleukin-6 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-6 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of interleukin-8 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-8 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interferon-alpha production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interferon-alpha production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interferon-beta production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interferon-beta production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interferon-gamma production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interferon-gamma production. Interferon-gamma is also known as type II interferon.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-1 alpha production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-1 alpha production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-1 beta production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-1 beta production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-1 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-1 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-10 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-10 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-12 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-12 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-17 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of production of any member of the interleukin-17 family of cytokines.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-18 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-18 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-2 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-2 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-4 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-4 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-6 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-6 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of interleukin-8 production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interleukin-8 production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of tumor necrosis factor production
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of tumor necrosis factor production.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of monooxygenase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the activity of a monooxygenase.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of ATPase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops or reduces the rate of ATP hydrolysis by an ATPase.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of ATPase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the rate of ATP hydrolysis by an ATPase.

gene.set.statistics.name: bile acid secretion
gene.set.statistics.description: The regulated release of bile acid, composed of any of a group of steroid carboxylic acids occurring in bile, by a cell or a tissue.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of DNA-templated transcription, elongation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription elongation, the extension of an RNA molecule after transcription initiation and promoter clearance by the addition of ribonucleotides catalyzed by a DNA-dependent RNA polymerase.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of DNA-templated transcription, elongation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of transcription elongation, the extension of an RNA molecule after transcription initiation and promoter clearance by the addition of ribonucleotides catalyzed by a DNA-dependent RNA polymerase.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of DNA-templated transcription, elongation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription elongation, the extension of an RNA molecule after transcription initiation and promoter clearance by the addition of ribonucleotides catalyzed by a DNA-dependent RNA polymerase.

gene.set.statistics.name: ribosome disassembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The disaggregation of a ribosome into its constituent components; includes the dissociation of ribosomal subunits.

gene.set.statistics.name: uropod organization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a uropod, a rigid membrane projection with related cytoskeletal components at the trailing edge of a lymphocyte or other cell in the process of migrating or being activated.

gene.set.statistics.name: receptor catabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a receptor molecule, a macromolecule that undergoes combination with a hormone, neurotransmitter, drug or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell function.

gene.set.statistics.name: low-density lipoprotein particle receptor catabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a low-density lipoprotein particle receptor molecule, a macromolecule that undergoes combination with a hormone, neurotransmitter, drug or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell function.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of low-density lipoprotein particle receptor catabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of low-density lipoprotein receptors.

gene.set.statistics.name: glomerular basement membrane development
gene.set.statistics.description: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the glomerular basement membrane over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The glomerular basement membrane is the basal laminal portion of the glomerulus which performs the actual filtration.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to insulin
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an insulin stimulus. Insulin is a polypeptide hormone produced by the islets of Langerhans of the pancreas in mammals, and by the homologous organs of other organisms.

gene.set.statistics.name: cellular response to insulin stimulus
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an insulin stimulus. Insulin is a polypeptide hormone produced by the islets of Langerhans of the pancreas in mammals, and by the homologous organs of other organisms.

gene.set.statistics.name: cellular response to hormone stimulus
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a hormone stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of stress-activated MAPK cascade
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction mediated by the stress-activated MAPK cascade.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of stress-activated MAPK cascade
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction mediated by the stress-activated MAPK cascade.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of stress-activated MAPK cascade
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction mediated by the stress-activated MAPK cascade.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of protein localization
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of microtubule-based process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any cellular process that depends upon or alters the microtubule cytoskeleton.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of vacuole fusion, non-autophagic
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the fusion of two vacuole membranes to form a single vacuole.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of viral transcription
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of viral transcription.

gene.set.statistics.name: circadian regulation of gene expression
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression such that an expression pattern recurs with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

gene.set.statistics.name: activin receptor signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of an extracellular ligand to an activin receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of superoxide anion generation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of enzymatic generation of superoxide by a cell.

gene.set.statistics.name: SREBP signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals from the endoplasmic reticulum to the nucleus generated as a consequence of decreased levels of one or more sterols (and in some yeast, changes in oxygen levels) and which proceeds through activation of a sterol response element binding transcription factor (SREBP) to result in up-regulation of target gene transcription.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of actin cytoskeleton organization
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.

gene.set.statistics.name: collagen metabolic process
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals. Collagen is highly enriched in glycine (some regions are 33% glycine) and proline, occurring predominantly as 3-hydroxyproline (about 20%).

gene.set.statistics.name: collagen biosynthetic process
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals. Collagen is highly enriched in glycine (some regions are 33% glycine) and proline, occurring predominantly as 3-hydroxyproline (about 20%).

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of collagen biosynthetic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of transcription elongation from RNA polymerase II promoter
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription elongation, the extension of an RNA molecule after transcription initiation and promoter clearance by the addition of ribonucleotides, catalyzed by RNA polymerase II.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of actin filament-based process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any cellular process that depends upon or alters the actin cytoskeleton.

gene.set.statistics.name: mitochondrial respiratory chain complex I assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form mitochondrial respiratory chain complex I.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of neutrophil apoptotic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of neutrophil apoptotic process.

gene.set.statistics.name: T cell differentiation in thymus
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a T cell via a differentiation pathway dependent upon transit through the thymus.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of T cell differentiation in thymus
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of T cell differentiation in the thymus.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of immature T cell proliferation in thymus
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of immature T cell proliferation in the thymus.

gene.set.statistics.name: mitochondrial respiratory chain complex assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a mitochondrial respiratory chain complex.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of RNA splicing
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of RNA splicing.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of RNA splicing
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of RNA splicing.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of histone phosphorylation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of one or more phosphate groups to a histone protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of histone phosphorylation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of one or more phosphate groups to a histone protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of glucokinase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glucokinase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a glucose molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of peptidyl-serine phosphorylation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the phosphorylation of peptidyl-serine.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of peptidyl-serine phosphorylation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the phosphorylation of peptidyl-serine.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of intracellular steroid hormone receptor signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of any intracellular steroid hormone receptor signaling pathway.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of an intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of an intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of an intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway.

gene.set.statistics.name: V(D)J recombination
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which immune receptor V, D, and J, or V and J gene segments, depending on the specific receptor, are recombined within a single locus utilizing the conserved heptamer and nonomer recombination signal sequences (RSS).

gene.set.statistics.name: T cell receptor V(D)J recombination
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which T cell receptor V, D, and J, or V and J gene segments, depending on the specific locus, are recombined within a single locus utilizing the conserved heptamer and nonomer recombination signal sequences (RSS).

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of histone ubiquitination
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of a ubiquitin group to a histone protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to vitamin E
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a vitamin E stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to ATP
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an ATP (adenosine 5'-triphosphate) stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: meiotic cytokinesis
gene.set.statistics.description: A cell cycle process that results in the division of the cytoplasm of a cell after meiosis, resulting in the separation of the original cell into two daughter cells.

gene.set.statistics.name: tumor necrosis factor-mediated signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a tumor necrosis factor to a receptor on the surface of a cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

gene.set.statistics.name: leptin-mediated signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of leptin to a receptor on the surface of a cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription. Leptin is a hormone manufactured primarily in the adipocytes of white adipose tissue, and the level of circulating leptin is directly proportional to the total amount of fat in the body.

gene.set.statistics.name: adiponectin-activated signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of adiponectin to a receptor on the surface of a cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of protein sumoylation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of SUMO groups to a protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of protein sumoylation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of SUMO groups to a protein.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to vitamin D
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a vitamin D stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: T-tubule organization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the T-tubule. A T-tubule is an invagination of the plasma membrane of a muscle cell that extends inward from the cell surface around each myofibril.

gene.set.statistics.name: Leydig cell differentiation
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a Leydig cell. A Leydig cell is a testosterone-secreting cell in the interstitial area, between the seminiferous tubules, in the testis.

gene.set.statistics.name: S-adenosylmethionine cycle
gene.set.statistics.description: A cyclic series of interconversions involving S-adenosylmethionine, S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine, L-cysteine, and L-methionine. Couples utilization of the methyl group of SAM with recycling of the homocysteinyl group and regeneration of methionine.

gene.set.statistics.name: protein localization to organelle
gene.set.statistics.description: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within an organelle.

gene.set.statistics.name: nitric oxide homeostasis
gene.set.statistics.description: A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of nitric oxide within an organism or cell.

gene.set.statistics.name: cholesterol biosynthetic process via desmosterol
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3 beta-ol, via the intermediate desmosterol.

gene.set.statistics.name: cholesterol biosynthetic process via lathosterol
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3 beta-ol, via the intermediate lathosterol.

gene.set.statistics.name: L-lysine catabolic process to acetyl-CoA via saccharopine
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of L-lysine into other compounds, including acetyl-CoA, via the intermediate saccharopine.

gene.set.statistics.name: histone H2B ubiquitination
gene.set.statistics.description: The modification of histone H2B by addition of ubiquitin groups.

gene.set.statistics.name: fatty acid beta-oxidation using acyl-CoA dehydrogenase
gene.set.statistics.description: A fatty acid beta-oxidation pathway in which the initial step of each oxidation cycle, which converts an acyl-CoA to a trans-2-enoyl-CoA, is catalyzed by acyl-CoA dehydrogenase; the electrons removed by oxidation pass through the respiratory chain to oxygen and leave H2O as the product. Fatty acid beta-oxidation begins with the addition of coenzyme A to a fatty acid, and ends when only two or three carbons remain (as acetyl-CoA or propionyl-CoA respectively).

gene.set.statistics.name: fatty acid beta-oxidation using acyl-CoA oxidase
gene.set.statistics.description: A fatty acid beta-oxidation pathway in which the initial step, which converts an acyl-CoA to a trans-2-enoyl-CoA, is catalyzed by acyl-CoA oxidase; the electrons removed by oxidation pass directly to oxygen and produce hydrogen peroxide, which is cleaved by peroxisomal catalases. Fatty acid beta-oxidation begins with the addition of coenzyme A to a fatty acid, and ends when only two or three carbons remain (as acetyl-CoA or propionyl-CoA respectively).

gene.set.statistics.name: cellular response to stress
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress. The stress is usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

gene.set.statistics.name: transferrin transport
gene.set.statistics.description: The directed movement of transferrin into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to testosterone
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a testosterone stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: mammary gland epithelial cell proliferation
gene.set.statistics.description: The multiplication or reproduction of mammary gland epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. Mammary gland epithelial cells make up the covering of surfaces of the mammary gland. The mammary gland is a large compound sebaceous gland that in female mammals is modified to secrete milk.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of mammary gland epithelial cell proliferation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mammary gland epithelial cell proliferation.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of mammary gland epithelial cell proliferation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of mammary gland epithelial cell proliferation.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of mammary gland epithelial cell proliferation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of mammary gland epithelial cell proliferation.

gene.set.statistics.name: mitochondrial proton-transporting ATP synthase complex assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a proton-transporting ATP synthase in the mitochondrial inner membrane.

gene.set.statistics.name: mitochondrial cytochrome c oxidase assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form respiratory chain complex IV (also known as cytochrome c oxidase) in the mitochondrial inner membrane.

gene.set.statistics.name: integrin activation
gene.set.statistics.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of an integrin, a heterodimeric adhesion receptor formed by the non-covalent association of particular alpha and beta subunits, that lead to the increased affinity of the integrin for its extracellular ligands.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of integrin activation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of integrin activation.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of cell adhesion mediated by integrin
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of cell adhesion mediated by integrin.

gene.set.statistics.name: cell-cell adhesion mediated by integrin
gene.set.statistics.description: The attachment of one cell to another cell via an integrin, a heterodimeric adhesion receptor formed by the non-covalent association of particular alpha and beta subunits.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation by symbiont of host apoptotic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process in which an organism stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death in the host, where programmed cell death proceeds by apoptosis. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of kinase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of kinase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of kinase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of kinase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

gene.set.statistics.name: nucleotide-excision repair, DNA incision
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that results in the endonucleolytic cleavage of the damaged strand of DNA. The incision occurs at the junction of single-stranded DNA and double-stranded DNA that is formed when the DNA duplex is unwound.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to glucagon
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a glucagon stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of NAD(P)H oxidase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the activity of the enzyme NAD(P)H oxidase.

gene.set.statistics.name: P-body assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins and RNA molecules to form a cytoplasmic mRNA processing body.

gene.set.statistics.name: stress granule assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins and RNA molecules to form a stress granule.

gene.set.statistics.name: CENP-A containing nucleosome assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The formation of nucleosomes containing the histone H3 variant CENP-A to form centromeric chromatin. This specialised chromatin occurs at centromeric region in point centromeres,  and the central core in modular centromeres.

gene.set.statistics.name: establishment of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which the sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome become joined along the entire length of the chromosome during S phase during a mitotic cell cycle.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to cytokine
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cytokine stimulus.

gene.set.statistics.name: erythrocyte homeostasis
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process of regulating the production and elimination of erythrocytes within an organism.

gene.set.statistics.name: homotypic cell-cell adhesion
gene.set.statistics.description: The attachment of a cell to a second cell of the identical type via adhesion molecules.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of homotypic cell-cell adhesion
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of homotypic cell-cell adhesion.

gene.set.statistics.name: heterotypic cell-cell adhesion
gene.set.statistics.description: The attachment of a cell to a cell of a different type via adhesion molecules.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of heterotypic cell-cell adhesion
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of heterotypic cell-cell adhesion.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of toll-like receptor 2 signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of toll-like receptor 2 signaling pathway.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of toll-like receptor 3 signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of toll-like receptor 3 signaling pathway.

gene.set.statistics.name: toll-like receptor 4 signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of binding to toll-like receptor 4.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of toll-like receptor 4 signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of toll-like receptor 4 signaling pathway.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of toll-like receptor 7 signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of toll-like receptor 7 signaling pathway.

gene.set.statistics.name: toll-like receptor 9 signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of binding to toll-like receptor 9.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of toll-like receptor 9 signaling pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of toll-like receptor 9 signaling pathway.

gene.set.statistics.name: positive regulation of maintenance of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that increases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a mitotic cell cycle.

gene.set.statistics.name: cellular response to amino acid starvation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of deprivation of amino acids.

gene.set.statistics.name: activation of protein kinase A activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive enzyme protein kinase A.

gene.set.statistics.name: protein hexamerization
gene.set.statistics.description: The formation of a protein hexamer, a macromolecular structure consisting of six noncovalently associated identical or nonidentical subunits.

gene.set.statistics.name: ion transmembrane transport
gene.set.statistics.description: A process in which an ion is transported across a membrane.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of transcription elongation from RNA polymerase II promoter
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of transcription elongation, the extension of an RNA molecule after transcription initiation and promoter clearance by the addition of ribonucleotides, catalyzed by RNA polymerase II.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of GTPase activity
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops or reduces the rate of GTP hydrolysis by a GTPase.

gene.set.statistics.name: Arp2/3 complex-mediated actin nucleation
gene.set.statistics.description: The actin nucleation process in which actin monomers combine to form a new branch on the side of an existing actin filament; mediated by the Arp2/3 protein complex and its interaction with other proteins.

gene.set.statistics.name: regulation of Arp2/3 complex-mediated actin nucleation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of actin nucleation mediated by the Arp2/3 complex and interacting proteins.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of Arp2/3 complex-mediated actin nucleation
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of actin nucleation mediated by the Arp2/3 complex and interacting proteins.

gene.set.statistics.name: cell junction assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: A cellular process that results in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a cell junction.

gene.set.statistics.name: adherens junction organization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an adherens junction. An adherens junction is a cell-cell junction composed of the epithelial cadherin-catenin complex at which the cytoplasmic face of the plasma membrane is attached to actin filaments.

gene.set.statistics.name: adherens junction assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an adherens junction. An adherens junction is a cell-cell junction composed of the epithelial cadherin-catenin complex at which the cytoplasmic face of the plasma membrane is attached to actin filaments.

gene.set.statistics.name: adherens junction maintenance
gene.set.statistics.description: The maintenance of an adherens junction. An adherens junction is a cell-cell junction composed of the epithelial cadherin-catenin complex at which the cytoplasmic face of the plasma membrane is attached to actin filaments.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to type I interferon
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a type I interferon stimulus. Type I interferons include the interferon-alpha, beta, delta, episilon, zeta, kappa, tau, and omega gene families.

gene.set.statistics.name: response to interferon-gamma
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interferon-gamma stimulus. Interferon-gamma is also known as type II interferon.

gene.set.statistics.name: negative regulation of glial cell apoptotic process
gene.set.statistics.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of glial cell apoptotic process.

gene.set.statistics.name: NAD biosynthesis via nicotinamide riboside salvage pathway
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NAD) from the vitamin precursor nicotinamide riboside.

gene.set.statistics.name: chylomicron assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The non-covalent aggregation and arrangement of proteins and lipids in the intestine to form a chylomicron.

gene.set.statistics.name: very-low-density lipoprotein particle assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The non-covalent aggregation and arrangement of proteins and lipids in the liver to form a very-low-density lipoprotein particle.

gene.set.statistics.name: high-density lipoprotein particle assembly
gene.set.statistics.description: The non-covalent aggregation and arrangement of proteins and lipids to form a high-density lipoprotein particle.

gene.set.statistics.name: low-density lipoprotein particle clearance
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which a low-density lipoprotein particle is removed from the blood via receptor-mediated endocytosis and its constituent parts degraded.

gene.set.statistics.name: high-density lipoprotein particle clearance
gene.set.statistics.description: The process in which a high-density lipoprotein particle is removed from the blood via receptor-mediated endocytosis and its constituent parts degraded.

gene.set.statistics.name: lipid droplet organization
gene.set.statistics.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a lipid particle.

gene.set.statistics.name: protein localization to cell surface
gene.set.statistics.description: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within the external part of the cell wall and/or plasma membrane.

gene.set.statistics.name: urate biosynthetic process
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of urate, the anion of uric acid, 2,6,8-trioxypurine.

gene.set.statistics.name: nuclear-transcribed mRNA catabolic process, exonucleolytic, 3'-5'
gene.set.statistics.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of the mRNA transcript body that occurs when the 3' end is not protected by a 3'-poly(A) tail; degradation proceeds in the 3' to 5' direction.

gene.set.statistics.name: cholesterol esterification
gene.set.statistics.description: A lipid modification process in which a sterol ester is formed by the combination of a carboxylic acid (often a fatty acid) and cholesterol. In the blood this process is associated with the conversion of free cholesterol into cholesteryl ester, which is then sequestered into the core of a lipoprotein particle.

gene.set.statistics.name: substrate adhesion-dependent cell spreading
